note_en:
My phone suddenly shows a notification from Firefox about Facebook or Mark Z. when I clicked on the notification, Firefox opened to show a page on blog.mozilla.org. The first article at the top is &#34;Use Your Voice to #StopHateForProfit&#34;.
  I don&#39;t object to receiving tips about product and feature; but I find it unacceptable that Firefox without my consent is pushing some campaign message to my phone. If Mozilla would like to push such messages, Firefox should have a new category under Notification, such as &#34;Campaign messages from Mozilla.org&#34;
   You need to  log in before you can comment on or make changes to this bug.
